The paper deals with transmission over a fading channel, which is a topic in information theory (cs.IT). The use of layered coding and successive refinement is a common technique in multimedia communication (cs.MM) and signal processing (cs.SI). The paper also discusses the impact of channel bandwidth and diversity, which are relevant topics in networked systems (cs.NI) and machine learning (cs.LG).
